## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Dense, unforgiving, solid.
    - Feedback: Very clear and direct. You know exactly where on the racket you hit the ball.
    - Hold vs. Release: Strong hold when hitting hard (due to the topsheet's mechanical grip), quick release on soft touches.
    - Dwell Time: Short on passive shots, surprisingly long when hitting with maximum power.

- Sound/Click: Not a loud, high-pitched clicky tensor. It produces a dense, muted thud or a sharp crack only upon maximum impact.

---

## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: (e.g., Viscaria style) Perfect for ultimate aggressive play and maximizing the speed of counter-spins.
    - Inner Carbon: Highly recommended to add a bit more dwell time and forgiveness to the 55° sponge.
    - All-Wood: 7-ply woods work nicely for players needing more control, but 5-ply woods may feel too slow and mushy.
    - Mismatch Cases: Soft, flexible 5-ply blades (the rubber is too heavy and hard) or extremely hard, stiff carbon blades (unless you are a professional).

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: The ideal placement. It requires the full body mechanics that the forehand stroke provides.
    - Backhand: Only for elite, high-level players with massive backhand swing speeds. For most, it is too hard and heavy.

